Stuttgart announced it was parting ways with Hannes Wolf on Sunday morning, the day after his side's 2-0 home defeat against second-place Schalke. Wolf has been in charge of the club for the past 16 months, bringing it back to the top flight of German football after Stuttgart's relegation in 2016. Read more: Bundesliga Matchday 20 roundup Bumpy return to top - Stuttgart lie in 15th place in the Bundesliga, three points above 16th place Werder Bremen. The side in 16th place faces a relegation playoff at the end of each season to preserve its top-flight status. - The Swabians have amassed only four points in their last eight league games, winning at home against Hertha Berlin and drawing away against Hannover. rc/tj (DPA, SID)